text: Aponoea pruinosella is a moth in the family Gelechiidae. It was described by Pierre Chrétien in 1915. It is found in Algeria.Aponoea at Markku Savela's Lepidoptera and Some Other Life Forms The wingspan is 11-12.5 mm.Annales de la Société Entomologique de France 84: 330 ==References== Category:Moths described in 1915 Category:Chelariini Category:Moths of Africa
